reviews.text: This is such a warm and welcoming museum with great history of the area. It was an Immigrant hotel & has a sample room that immigrants would have slept in. I love the "step into their shoes" exhibit with stories of real immigrants.

Its a really great place to learn about German heritage. You don't have to be German to participate in there very enriching programs. 

 Trips, classes, events all kind of events. The museum is self guided for touring. It costs $5 per person. 

 Memberships are $35 dollars a month. Davenport was first settled by German immigrants. It is really neat to learn about history and culture. You should check it out.
We liked..specially Christmas celebration in Germany. Also their souvenir shop is nice .
This place is AMAZING! I had never been there, and was pleasantly surprised at the displays and the gift shop! Check it out for that hard to shop for person on your list!
Fun museum. Will be back
I love all of the outdoor events that they hold here! The view of the river is spectacular too! Just watch out for all of the addicts and homeless people when there isn't an event going on.
Love this place. River, great view and gorgeous band shell. Great place for outdoor concerts.
QC Pops concert is always good and bring your picnic gear!
Just finished setting up stage for orchestra summer pops concert
Davenport Iowa is a very good place for people of retirement to me but I'd rather be in Columbus Ohio where I'm from it's not big enough in this state for me I give your place 3 stars

Putnam Museum and Science Center is a wonderful place for any families looking for a smaller museum to visit. It has all sorts of different exhibits and experiences, from meeting dinosaurs to playing a laser harp. The employees are great, the concessions are convenient, and the gift shop is full of goodies. I'd very much recommend it.

Very neat and organized museum I've ever visited so far! Staff is very welcoming and friendly! A great variety of exhibits, the giant screen and the choice sample was great. Kids really enjoyed! Keep up the good work!!

My two young boys & myself love to go to the museum! It keeps us busy for several hours & is affordable. It is good for kids 3 & up but my 2 year old still has a lot of fun. Don't miss the virtual reality area!!

I have never seen a museum with so much hands on exhibits for the kids, it was a truly fun experience! If this place was closer to my home I would be there all the time! My kids had a blast ! Reasonable prices and the movies they were showing , I wanted to see them all! Highly recommend!!!
My kids loved playing with all the hands on things. If adults want to look at stuff and get into depth it’s best not to go with kids. I overall enjoyed myself though!

Amazing place for tree climbing, I've been coming here since I was very young. It is a bit disappointing to be around water, like the Rose Garden fountain, the Stone Fountain, and the duck pond, and not be allowed to play in any of it. Maybe a water feature intended to be played with would reduce the amount of young children who, even when watched by their parents, fully ignore the signs not to get into the fountain and do just that. Beyond that, there are some sort of scary people who hang out there after dark, but I don't think they're supposed to be there anyway.

This is a wonderful place to come visit and see some interesting plants. They offer special tours if you arrange ahead of time otherwise the staff is always willing to answer questions and help you out with whatever you need. I've seen them do cuttings for kids to help them start their own garden. Wonderful place

I've never spent so much time at a park in my life. I've spent countless hours...Laughing, and just enjoying my children. I lost my best friend and my son's dad 10 years ago and the last time I ever saw him was at the park. We spent hours that day. I will forever cherish in my heart those memories . ♥️♥️♥️

Such a versatile park. It is the Quad Cities' mini central park with sidewalks around it, tons of green space for picnics, concerts, & movies in the park, and a fun conservatory. Plus tons of spots for pictures or weddings.

Playground, walking paths, the indoor & outdoor gardens... My kids love seeing the ducks in the pond best of all. My toddler especially enjoys telling the ducks when it's time to fly South and migrate.

We came to this bar for our first time to see "White Walls Band". The staff was incredible. They found us a table when apparently there we none. Never waited to get a drink and the food was great. White Walls is a top notch band, and we enjoyed their guest performers
Very much. We will be back!
Great place with solid menu. Indoor and outdoor seating, great atmosphere and friendly staff. We enjoy going here with the family.

went to creekside to watch the performance of 'The Insiders Band' ... great place, both the outdoor sitting area with picnic-style benches and the indoor bar and grill .. the servers at the bar were gracious and quick, even though there were a LOT of people .. large assortment of beers in bottles as well as on tap.. the surrounding area outside the bar is BEAUtiful !
Always a good time. Good food. Decent beer selection.
Very tavern-like ... Drinks not expensive, and good dance music on weekends

They make a fresh delicious sandwich. The bread is baked fresh daily and the meat and cheese is sliced right when you order. They have a good selection of classic sandwich toppings such as onions, pickles, mustard, mayo, etc. Unfortunately their prices are definitely on the high-end for a sandwich shop.
Sandwiches were on point and the tea is super great! Polite staff and relaxed atmosphere. Planning to go again soon :)
Love the staff here- they love to make their food, and provide great service each and ever time. The food is delicious, and very reasonably priced. This is one of my favorite places to go in Ames!
I enjoy the customer service. It also has a pleasant atmosphere.
The best sub in the Midwest! Fresh-sliced meats and cheese with a number of options to choose from. Always a line, but worth the wait.

It's not the fanciest or prettiest buffet ever. Could use a decor and seating update. But the food is good and there's a large variety to choose from. They have everything from sushi and frog legs to typical "Chinese" picks with chicken, pork, seafood. Several soup choices. Nice selection of fresh fruit and veggies. The pot stickers are amazing. It's a busy and popular location especially on evenings and weekends. Handicap accessible and they have booths or chairs for seating.
My first stop at a Chinese buffet is the sushi table. They offer many many choices. Most however we're not to my liking.  The rest of the servings leave me very satisfied.The service is fantastic!

I try to eat here often. If you like Chinese food this is your place to eat. They have a huge buffet, which includes sushi and a grill. They serve a variety of seafood as well, including shrimp prepared several ways, raw oysters, and king crab claws. There is something for everyone here.
It was amazing. Their service was great. When my daughter drop her lobster in her drink they gave us a new one.

Food: normal Chinese buffet style food. Nothing spectacular, but taste fine, seemed fresh. The egg drop soup was awesome. I’d recommend the hot tea! The only problem I had was the buffet hadn’t been restocked fast enough so a lot of the items I wanted were gone.

Building: building and bathroom were clean. No complaints here.

Staff: The staff was nice and friendly. Refilled my cup often.

Time:1200-100pm

Stars: only 4 stars because a lot of the food was empty.

This is one of my favorite restaurants. The food is always amazing, and there are so many options.  The wait staff and hosts are very attentive and nice. Service is quick and friendly.  One suggestion I have would be bigger appetizer servings for large groups.

Absolutely love this place! Food wise I have not had a bad meal and I’ve tried a few different things now. Always delicious and flavorful. My only request is that management install at least one baby changing table in at least the women’s restroom. Obviously it’s more of an adult restaurant but when I was there last weekend I was actually not the only gal in there with a baby. My 6 mo decided she wanted to do her business before the meal was served and trying to change a messy diaper was ridiculous. I had to lay her on a chair in the restroom and hope she didn’t roll onto the floor as I grabbed a couple more wipes. 

Install a changing table and you can have all the stars you want!
I happened upon this restaurant by accident and what a happy one it was. Flavorful food and decent sake. If you're in the mood for interesting Asian cuisine, give it a try.
Delicious food. Had Tempura green beans, mango stir fried rice and pad thai.
The atmosphere is plush, calming and colorful. One of the best Asian fusion places I've been in. The service was great.

Wow!  Service is as great as the food is. Best Deli I have eaten at.  Will keep going back to try different things. Thank you Ross  and staff for all your great service and friendly atmosphere.  Everyone that walked in was greated. You can tell they have many repeat customers.   Now a new one!
Had the #14 Turkey Reuben. They were fantastic! Loaded with meat! A hidden gem on the end of the Village of East Davenport! A must for a great sandwich!
Blow you away tasty sandwiches. Blindingly fast service. Amazing potato salad. Don't be put off if it looks crowded. There is extra seating upstairs.
Best sandwiches I’ve ever had. Great little spot. East Village Davenport gem. Highly recommend.
Had this for the first time today. Hands down best sandwich I have ever had! LOVED IT!

I went here expecting some pizza , but what I found was incredible , while walking in the door I slipped on some peanut butter hitting the lever to the basement. It had been five months and I had no food. The last of the rats were gone and I was gonna die . But at the top of the tunnel I could see a man using 1.7 percent of his power. It was the great Nate he swooped down crowning me in his bosom , I could Taste the cool sweat running of his forehead as we zoned foreword . Antonella’s best sex slave I’ve ever had!

Wonderful family restaurant. Loved the pasta , with meatballs but over time have tried the whole menu.  Its all delicious. My dad was old school Italian he loved it.
The service is friendly and knowledgeable. I'll be back.

Great creamy garlic salad dressing and veal parmigiana. They also only do straws on request and they are paper - thanks for thinking of the environment! The tiramisu is also great. Definitely try this if you want Italian in the QC.

Nice, quiet restaurant with very good pizza.
Reasonably priced.
We go here almost once a week. I either get the all you can eat spaghetti or a calzone. The service is always great and the staff is very nice. I would recommend.

Walking into the place I wasn't sure what to expect, but what a treat this place is.  The staff is unbelievable.  Everyone knows the menu and can describe the detailed items that accompany the meals.  The way they make a show of their menu is unique and entertaining.  The food is absolutely exceptional.  I had the lamb chops and the were not only cooked to perfection, but seasoned that way as well.  I can't give this place a high enough rating.

Duck City Bistro provided the absolute best prime rib I've ever had. Perfectly seasoned and cooked medium rare. Overall a great experience. The wife had a filet and said it was cooked perfect as well. Food prices weren't as high as I was expecting but alcohol caught me by surprise. Would recommend for the intimate experience alone.

The food is amazing. The chef comes out and shows you all of the featured dishes before you are seated. Fancy, and actually fairly reasonably priced. Walked in and got a 2 top on Sat night with only 10 min wait. Definitely recommend!
Great atmosphere! An owner with so much charisma I enjoyed watching him float around the restaurant. Very welcoming, amazing food, and the place I'd go for upscale dining to enjoy my night.
One word: awesome. Go. If you enjoy laughing, letting loose, and enjoying good food just go. Tell Jeremy hi.

Great meal this evening! Lemongrass soup with shrimp was delicious. Our entrees were excellent. She enjoyed the Chicken Rama on a bed of steamed veggies with brown rice. I chose the Crying Tiger: New York strip on bed of salad greens, topped with sauteed asparagus spears. Hot spicy dish that you can personally dial-up till the tears flow.
The appetizer platter was a feast for the eyes. The fried rice-noodle-wrapped shrimp looked very interesting but were rather dry to the taste.
The chicken satay, spring rolls, and vegetable rolls were very tasty!
Our sole reason for driving 40 minutes to visit this restaurant was the Angel Wings advertised on their web site.
When we arrived, were disappointed to learn this item is no longer part of their menu.
Our waitress was very helpful and kind. 
Would definitely dine here again.

Very good. Big selection on the menu is very nice especially sense some of my friends are more picky . It's a fun place to try a little of everything . Very clean and nice relaxing atmosphere.  Very friendly and helpful staff.  Good date location or casual dining.  It's a lil small so reservations would be a good idea . Definitely a place I would go back with friends and family.

So YUMMY!!! I was addicted from the first time! 
Must try the lettuce cups! They even made it vegan for me! Also ate them with sticky rice as I’m a huge sticky rice fan! Perfect amount! The starter is all you need! I was so full by the end of it! Affordable and satisfying! The staff are amazing too! Highly recommend and I will be back when I’m in town!!! I’m drooling just thinking about it!!! Thanks for the great food and great service !

Passing through town and found you --- fantastic discovery!!! Such welcoming service and excellent meal. THANK YOU!!!! We will definitely stop by again next time. Appetizers - excellent - main courses delicious and the welcoming attitude and attention were a delight.

Came in. Ordered a drink. There were only two stools at the bar. My waitress was nice. Ordered the pad see ew. Decided it was too busy, place was too small, and not enough entertainment for one person, so I told my waitress I wanted my food too go. I get the food, get in the car, drive home. I open it and find that the container is HALF-FULL, it has CHICKEN instead of TOFU (mind you, I'm not a super strict vegetarian, but if I was, there would be hell to pay. Plus, if someone has an allergy, that's just not cool.), and I paid $13 plus tip for it. So. That completely ruined it all. 1 star because the food was actually okay.

Awesome food, meat fall off the bone ribs and giant Wings.  All drenched in the sauce of your choice.
Man I tell you, there is nothing that you chose on the menu, that you can go wrong with!!
Sit at the bar and you won't be disappointed by the service.  I don't know where they found all these fine ladies to tend bar here, but all I can say is, "they stay hopping all night long!!"

Four of us stopped for lunch on Saturday about 1pm. The restaurant was busy with about 15 minute wait. Our wait time was spent enjoying the multitude of filling station memorabilia. The food was very good. The staff was very efficient and friendly. It was worth the short wait.

Atmosphere seemed unique. Menu was large and a little all over the place. We shared the cheese curds. Way over priced for the amount received as an app. Then I had the Oriental chicken salad. Dressing was off, not Asian at all. Chicken on the salad was non-existent, all batter and no meat. To top it all off, 40% of my lettuce leaves were rotten. The waitress only came by twice, so I picked out the bad food and tried to eat around it. I won't be back and I will not be recommending it to anyone.
Great service. Great burgers. Fries not as hot as I like. As they do cool quickly.

We scheduled a group event around lunch time. Staff: The staff was awesome and our waitress was on top of it. A++ service. Food: the food is great. I recommend the Filing Station burger with French fries. They also have popcorn for free next to the bar! Building: The dinning area is clean and spaced nicely. Bonus: the burgers have eggs on them and they have a bar! Star rating: 5 stars because the food was priced right, it came out fast for a group of 15 and the service was awesome! I’d give the service 5 stars by itself!

We attended a retirement party hosted upstairs.  Staff was very friendly and provided good service after taking orders.  Only issue was staff was not available for long periods at times through the night to place orders.

I am super sick and all i wanted was soup. and your Tortilla Soup really hit the spot. My gf picked it up and brought it home and it arrived hot and with crunchy chips. The soup has a great depth of flavor without being to spicy. I would order this again. I just wish it came in a bigger container, so i had more.
Great spot for Sunday lunch and beer. Lots of TVs to be able to watch different games. Weekday specials look to be good. Going back to have to see for myself!

We had pizza, again thank you Cub Scout Pack664!! You guys know how to do It!  Their Coaches are the best! I love food and was totally impressed!! The pizza was great! I once had a calzone from here.  I told my friends and others about it,  will always remember!  😊Great service, staff was very attentive. Smiles greeted you coming and going! Great job Jersey.......
Cuban Panini is the best!!! Great variety of food on the menu for a fair price as well!

Food was great! Service was not at this visit. Margarita was watery and the waitress said it was because she was new. Wasn't checked on by her till we were done eating has to ask other waiters for silverware, napkins and to fix the margaritas. Would eat here again but I'll stick with water.

We came here for a birthday dinner, we had a table of 9. It took about 15 minutes for our drinks and the iced tea tasted really weird. The waiter was not very attentive at all. We had to go up to the front counter to ask for silverware because our waiter was nowhere to be found. It took about an hour for him to take our order and took about an hour to get our food. By the time we got our food my plate and my sister in laws plate of food were ice cold. We were extremely disappointed because at the other locations the food and service are excellent.
Pretty good Mexican, decent service, sometimes forget details on orders. Good in house salsa. Authentic tamales.
Wonderful food. Great service. Reasonable prices. good location.

I love this restaurant for 3 reasons. The first is the cleanliness, the second is the staff, and last but certainly not least is the amazing food. Honestly I think the salsa is the main reason I go there. ♥️

I have been going to this place since 2012. They keep reducing the amount of rice served each time. Finally it is not worth the price. The chefs are nice and all that but what about the food ? Last thanksgiving we found hair in the soup. They replaced our  soup and salad for free but dang. We used to love coming here but not anymore.

We sat at the hibachi grill and it was wonderful. Our chef seemed to be having fun as well and was playful when interacting with us. I got the chicken and shrimp and they we're both so good. I also tried the steak which was excellent. It's a ton of food so definitely come hungry. You can still order off the menu here so we got some spicy tuna rolls. The hibachi does have a tofu and vegetable option if you're vegetarian, they also have lots of tofu on the main menu.

Fun place. Held a work dinner here and a birthday celebration for my kid. The flames kind of freaked out my youngest child, which was equal parts tragic and adorable. Paid around $500 for 12 people so not cheap. Tasty food.

Giving a 5star review because it usually is amazing .. and so fun for kiddos ... but last night was HORRIBLE.. food was 1/2 fast and service was poor. Our waitress was great... we had a reservation at 630 got seated at the grill at 632 — didn’t see our cook until almost 8:00. That’s AFTER I went to someone else’s table and started yelling at them. They did give us 50% off the meal... hopefully next time will be better.
Great food and service. Cool staff, and the chefs knew some cool tricks with their utensils, like throwing the food at you and you'd have to catch it with your mouth. 👍🏽

I was at a large party in their party room so I can only speak of the food and not of the service. The food was fantastic. A great salad and perfect salmon. Others in my group said the prime rib was perfect. I know it looked perfect. I recommend giving it a try.

We (my boyfriend and I) got there tonight at 6 and got seated at the bar. It was slow since it’s a Monday, there were never more than 5 people sitting at the actual bar. It took our server what seemed like 10 minutes to even acknowledge we were there and she was standing behind the bar making drinks. She came and we ordered everything at one time. We got our drinks (water and a sprite) and our salads just fine. Next thing we are getting our meals but we had ordered an appetizer too. Which she forgot about and then came out after our main meal got to us. She never came around or even yelled over bar to ask if we were okay or to check on us. We never got refills on our drinks. Seemed like she was more concerned about the people at the bar. The only “good” thing she did was help box up our leftover appetizer. Not sure if we will come back but if we do, we definitely won’t be sitting in the bar area.

From the hostess to the wait staff to the freaking food (We had brunch) was excellent. Was headed to Cracker Barrel but saw this place first. I'm so glad we stopped here first. There was not one thing on the buffet that we didn't enjoy. The waiter made us feel as if we were in a platinum restaurant. As far as I'm concerned it is. We didn't have to ask for anything as he was attentive and kept us happy. Thanks Thunder Bay Grill for the best buffet experience to this day and we've been to a lot of buffets. We will be back our next trip back into Iowa.

Great service and wonderful food. The place was really cool looking too! Definitely an upscale fine dining experience, high end food with prices to match but worth it for sure. Only thing I didn't care for was the biscuits they bring to the table, they were pretty hard and served with cinnamon butter which didn't seem to go with a biscuit to me.

Ate there a couple times food is excellent I think if you haven't tried it you should go eat dinner there guarantee you'll love it nicer and bigger better establishment well maintained last time I visited I was hunting for painted rocks 4 the one who has passed keeping memories alive so if you haven't tried painting rocks and hiding them  it's pretty awesome.  And memories alive  and you'd be amazed how far a rock can go and return  my nephew's Baby Hawk Newberry Rocks has went all around the world went to the UK, Paris they took a picture holding his Rock in front of Paris tower is really amazing then ended up in Wisconsin Minnesota and back around Quad Cities but everyone you should come see Thunder Bay Grille enjoy yourself I guarantee you I love the food

The new owners (as of Oct 2014) have done a great job.   Sushi was delicious and was served in a way that every table kept getting served as the sushi was prepared.   So no one was left waiting while other tables received 3 plates of sushi and you have none as is usually done.  Brilliant!   The wait staff was charming and attentive. Will definitely be back.

This is by far my favorite Sushi restaurant! I have been there several times and have not once been disappointed. The sushi chef really knows what he is doing, It's very interesting to see how everything is made. The staff is wonderful, very fun and welcoming! I am excited to try their Hibachi next time. Every time I am there, the people look like they are having a blast. Definitely a place I would recommend to everyone!

I had an absolutely wonderful experience at Ichiban Sushi and Steak House. I have only had the sushi from Ichiban and not the hibachi, but I plan on trying the hibachi soon. Speaking from a sushi perspective, I am a sushi connoisseur and the sushi here is artful and beautiful as well as incredibly delicious and addicting. I plan on making this my regular sushi spot, hands down. This is by far the best sushi I think I have ever had.

Went for the buy one get one free hibachi at lunch on a Monday at 12:15pm. The wait staff put the "buy one get one" offer in front of us when we sat down.  In very small print at the bottom of the placard, it says "dinner menu only" however, this was never verbally conveyed to us.  We were there for lunch.  We ordered hibachi.  After our order was taken, we were told that the hibachi chef was "off" and would it be ok if they cooked in back.  Sure.  The meal was mediocre at best.  The entire meal was definitely not "grilled" hibachi style.  It was semi cold, as if it had been warmed up.  The meat had no grill char on it.  The rice was clearly from a large pot of rice, and the veggies from a large vat of boiling veggies in sauce.  The soup appetizer had no flavor and actually tasted rather musty.  The bill?  $33.00 for two with a 15% gratuity added on already for us...my guess in anticipation of their ruse being discovered once the bill was delivered and we had no choice.  Have liked their food in the past, but will never, ever return.  I will be contacting their corporate offices.  No wonder we were the only ones in the place.  That should have tipped us off right there.
Amazing! Love it.

This may be my favorite restaurant in the Quad Cities. The lemon gimlets are to die for. I love that he changes his menu so I can come in and have a different experience every time. I highly recommend Woodfire to everyone I know. Absolutely will return, probably several times!

The food is always incredible here but that crab cake was out of this world. It's hard to get good seafood in the Quad Cities but Woodfire nailed it. The lemon gimlet is delicious. The staff is always very friendly. I love that the menu changes and that the chef obviously loves what he does.

Great burger and prime rib.  Great chef, Toby.  Amazing value for the money! This our favorite place to go out and eat at for dinner.  Everything is amazing and great portion size.  The drinks are delicious and the service is amazing.  Anyone looking for a casual or wine and dine kinda place, Woodfire grill is the best.  I would definitely recommend the Braised beef and Cesar salad!

Came here to get away from the St. Patty's insanity and we were quite surprised! Upscale looking on the inside, and the bartender was great. Also tried the Pepperjack crab dip and Jalapeno wontons - DELICIOUS! Definitely liked this place and would come back!
The prime rib is my fave one. It's so delicious! Everybody must try.

3/8/19 ordered pizza at 605pm said it will be 45 to a hr. Cool. Hour and half later still not here! Called Rockingham store manager didn't know what happened! Said I will call you back I'm calling my driver. The driver called me said he lost my ticket! My bad I will be bringing them. It's free anyways. Damn right it gonna be free! 3 kids at home and I have to be up at 4am for work!! Manager never called me back! Lost my business! I will go to Casey's pizza in davenport or tc pizza in Milan!! Or uncle bills!!! I dont even wanna give them 1 star!
Usually love Happy Joe's Pizza, but the food was old, and cold. Terrible! The customer service was the only good experience.

Great pizza. We have small family get togethers there .... very accommodating. Happy Joe's is a local iconic pizza place. There are several in the area. Some have a kids play area "jungle bungle" Not the cheapest pizza but very good.
The pizza was great and the service was good ... no complaints
Food is good especially baked pasta .prompt delivery service fair prices.

My daughter and I love this place. She loves the arcade and play land.. And I love the food. We had her 7th birthday party there and you can rent a room for FREE, you just pay for your food and games. It was nice compared to every where else where its at least $100 just to rent a party room with nothing else included. All around a good place!
A nice environment for children. Friendly staff and good food. This location offers a gaming area, wall climbing, and a gymnasium in the basement. They do not offer ice cream, only frozen yogurt.
FANTASTIC place for a birthday celebration! Wonderful, friendly staff. Great Quad Cities food. And a whole lotta fun for the kids!!! This is THE go-to place for birthday fun for my kids

If I could give 0 stars I could. This place is a complete joke and my family and I will NEVER return. We ordered 20 dollars worth of tokens for our kids to play only to get downstairs to be harassed by 3 different people asking where our wrist bands were this was after we spent 80 dollars on food and drinks. We said we didn’t know you needed them because we just bought tokens! They were completely rude and when the manager said he would take care of it we waited 20 minutes for him to come back so we left and will never go back. DO NOT GO HERE
A little pricey but well worth the price for the happiness of the kids! My children absolutely love this place! Good pizza is just a added bonus!

Quick service and delicious quad city pizza. Found myself in the area and decided to check them out. Was not disappointed, word to the wise though, no need to add extra cheese. Got a pepperoni, sausage and extra cheese pie and the herd of cows that donated their deliciousness to cover my toppings were beyond any and all expectations, almost too much cheese as odd as that sounds. Will definitely check out next time I find myself in the QC.
Some of the best pizza I've ever had. Really great service, great menu, and just overall really good place to eat!

We came during lunch and it wasn't busy.  I brought my two youngest and we had great service and great sausage pizza.  We were greeted by two sweet ladies, when we entered and our waitress was awesome.  We will definitely return.
Amazing Quad Cities Style pizza. A must visit if you're in the area. Fair prices, amazing food
We were waited on right away and our server was very sweet. Food tasted delicious!  We were in and out at our own pace.
The young lady named lady nickname I should say what's a great help to me keep up the good job
Great sandwiches! I highly suggest a letter D with Chicken and a cheddar fry combo! They also have great baked potatoes and soups.
Good sandwiches, loaded potatoes and waffle fries. Great bread. Good lunch spot or quick pick up spot. Good location. Friendly people
One of the workers kids was in there yesterday acting a fool and demanding money from the mom. Then the kid peeled out of the parking lot in their car and almost ran over a grandma.

My bill came out to $30, lady at the counter rudely stated , we can't take that $100 , the only money I had on me. I guess I wouldn't have had such a problem if they were polite about it, I felt like I committed a crime by paying with the only form of payment I had
The young lady named lady nickname I should say what's a great help to me keep up the good job
Great sandwiches! I highly suggest a letter D with Chicken and a cheddar fry combo! They also have great baked potatoes and soups.
Good sandwiches, loaded potatoes and waffle fries. Great bread. Good lunch spot or quick pick up spot. Good location. Friendly people
One of the workers kids was in there yesterday acting a fool and demanding money from the mom. Then the kid peeled out of the parking lot in their car and almost ran over a grandma.

My bill came out to $30, lady at the counter rudely stated , we can't take that $100 , the only money I had on me. I guess I wouldn't have had such a problem if they were polite about it, I felt like I committed a crime by paying with the only form of payment I had

Probably the best restaurant I’ve ever been too mostly because of the workers that are there. I had an interaction with one of the employees who made a big impact on the way I view restaurant workers. He was a very hard worker. He was a bus boy at the time but he said that he also takes his part in the cooking of the food (and the food was absolutely delicious). I complemented his work and I remember him very well mostly because we have the same name. Overall the service was great. A lot of big smiles and warm greeting. Food came out quick and I was surprised. Tasted very fresh and I enjoyed it very much. The outside eating is a great touch and it overlooks the village as well as a ball park where you can catch a game if you come at the right time. Upstairs seating is also very cool. The front of the building looking very cool. All around best place I’ve ever been to
Service was great on a Sunday afternoon with a newbie waiter who made sure we received everything we needed. Apps & drinks were awesome, mystery beer for a $1 was a nice surprise!
I dont like that you have to pay for chips and salsa and the food is just fine. But the service was great! Sally was wonderful!

A Quad City staple... While not most "authentic" ethnic restaurant... The food is fast, consistently good. This particular location is in historic East Village. There's a hip vibe here. Full bar is available. There's a nice range f seating from sitting at the bar, booths, tables with stools. Nice views of a local park as well.
Great food and even better service! You have to visit Skippy and sit in the bar area. He is the best.

Probably the best restaurant I’ve ever been too mostly because of the workers that are there. I had an interaction with one of the employees who made a big impact on the way I view restaurant workers. He was a very hard worker. He was a bus boy at the time but he said that he also takes his part in the cooking of the food (and the food was absolutely delicious). I complemented his work and I remember him very well mostly because we have the same name. Overall the service was great. A lot of big smiles and warm greeting. Food came out quick and I was surprised. Tasted very fresh and I enjoyed it very much. The outside eating is a great touch and it overlooks the village as well as a ball park where you can catch a game if you come at the right time. Upstairs seating is also very cool. The front of the building looking very cool. All around best place I’ve ever been to
Service was great on a Sunday afternoon with a newbie waiter who made sure we received everything we needed. Apps & drinks were awesome, mystery beer for a $1 was a nice surprise!
I dont like that you have to pay for chips and salsa and the food is just fine. But the service was great! Sally was wonderful!

Heard tales of deliciousness about the great Rudy's Taco.... Service was fine. Food was fine. Maybe it just wasn't their day when I visited but it didn't seem like a place to write home about. It was average at best that day. Really have heard great things though I just didn't see that greatness when I visited... Location is everything and this one is not the best in town. Those great tales were spun about a different location.
The Monday $5 small combo special is a great deal! Amanda Is so sweet, treats you like a real friend! Love it here, its gotta be the best Rudy's in the chain!😍
Always enjoy the ice cream here. The texture is more like grandma's homemade vs soft serve. Service is quick and the drive thru helps too! Inside has a nice cafe feel to it.

Fabulous Staff and very clean  food is good. Beware, ice cream can give you brain freeze brrrrr. Small price to pay for very customer oriented staff. 5 stars plus, Karen is outstanding this location is fortunate to have an employee of her caliber these days!
Absolutely love this place always friendly service and you can use your imagination to come up with different shakes because they have so many combination options, I go there all the time.
Best ice craem place around, better then Whitey's by far.
Always a great time. Friendly staff and owner. Have standard flavors and always rotating new or special flavors. Gotta check out the doors!!!
